      "type": "teach",
      "title": "Stress decides",
      "body": "English squeezes the vowels it doesn’t stress. Say “banana” — only the middle a keeps its full sound: 𐑚𐑩𐑯𐑭𐑯𐑩. Shavian spells the squeeze honestly, which is why so many words are full of 𐑩 no matter how English letters them."
